> most of my animations run from between 30 and 60 fps (A2500/030/882)
>. Prolly jus' another piss poor C portover from another lackadasical 
>programmer trying to cut corners for the higher profit margins!

No, Frontier was developed on Amiga...
I think you're a bit confused here. Texture mapping has nothing to do with
the chipset. It is done with CPU, and can be done on any platform.
The problem is that texture mapping is much faster when you have the
graphics stored as chunky pixels, and Amiga uses planar graphics. You
either have to do the mapping in planar, which is SLOW, or render the
picture in chunky pixel, and then convert the pic into planar. With fast
Amigas the latter can be done in kind-of realtime, but it doesn't leave
much time for anything else.
So, it's texturemapping is not a problem. Doing it fast is.
