instead of any messages. These are presented as articles, complete with buttons,
but these do nothing when clicked. Current theory suggests that if the last
bulletin board viewing before launch is the bottom of the board, thanb this bug
occurs. (guess.) The problem is easily fixed by fast-forwarding to the next day.

2) 'Attacks' INSIDE space stations.
This one can be quite nasty. Whilst docked at a station I purchased a Python,
intending to use it for passenger transporting as well as cargo. I had a Tiger
Trader at the time, and hence needed two more crew (see the SUGGESTIONS section).
One crew member was soon accquired, but another was not available. After
fast-forwarding for well over two months of game time, none had become available.
I decided to take on a passenger in the hope that this would free space on the
board for a JOB WANTED ad. My passsenger was wanted by some corp. or other. About
one game week later (still no crew) a ship turned up outside the station sending
the message "You'll regret dealing with x....". I ignored it, and went to fast
forward to next day. SHIP UNDER ATTACK!! I was unable to fast forward. Bugger.
OK, I thought, sell the ship and get a smaller one. "Cannot sell ship with
passengers on board." Double bugger. I was, as far as I can tell, irretrievably
stuck. NASTY.

3) Manual/ code mis-types.
There are several of these, but two spring to mind:
a) The Tiger Trader is listed in the manual as having 1 gun mounting. In the game
it has three. (This is probably a manual error- the gun turret works perfectly.)
b) The Imperial Trader is listed as having 6 crew, but in the game needs only
one. (this is definitely a mis-type in the code- the damn thing is a 700+
tonner!!)

4) Peculiar graphics bug.
I apologise for this one, because it is somewhat vague. However, with certain
ships, firing the front laser sometimes produces very odd on-screen effects- as
if the laser were being fired from the middle of the view window, or as if the
laser were being fired FROM the target AT the view window. On one occaison I even
had the smoke effect coming from the front of my Imp. Trader as I looked at it
firing from the outside view. As far as I can tell, the flashing orange beacon
outside some space stations seems to cause this if it is in the view window. (In
case it is useful, the worst occurence of this was at Shifnalport at Diso.
Despite the 'hit/damage' graphical effect, my ship took no damage. Also, in this
case the effect only occurred when my laser should have been hitting the
station...)

5) Missile velocity effects.
I dont know if this is truly a bug or not, but when firing missiles my ship (an
Imp. Trader) appears to be 'pulled' forwards slightly. The effect is most
noticeable when flying very slowly or stationary. I don't know if this is
intentional (the missile's engine firing just before it is released) or a bug
(the effect being supposed to be some kind of 'recoil', but happening backwards.)

Thats most of the bugs I can remeber right now =)
Some others have been posted, but I don't believe I have met any of them. NOW, on
to the :
           NOT REALLY BUGS BUT DAMN ANNOYING ANYWAY SECTION
            COMES FREE WITH HELPFUL(?) SUGGESTIONS!!

1) The complete inability of Vipers to launch without crashing into each other!
This is silly. If I shoot at a space station from behind, the vipers all launch
and either hit each other, or hit the station. Other aberrations include Vipers
crashing into the ground when I am flying in a sedate straight line.

2) The tendancy of computer pilots to ram.
Don't get me wrong, this is not always a bad thing. Many posters to this group
advocate ramming with a big ship as a good way to take out opponents, and I
really felt it when a Panther Clipper I was trying to assassinate decided to fly
through me! However, many small ships (especially those damn Vipers) insist on
ramming my Imperial Trader with 30 shield generators and an Energy Booster Unit.
Needless to say, they barely make a dent. I am NOT deliberately ramming them
either (I usually fight in engines off mode, only thrusting when badly hit.)

3) Crew. This is ridiculous, and EXTREMELY ANNOYING! Case in point. Go to Achenar
(Strictly Capitalist with NO SOCIAL SAFEGUARDS) or any other planet for that
matter, and you find it VERY HARD INDEED to get more than 1 Crew member at a
time. Here I am in my Tiger Trader. I see a Python (2 more crew). Do I dare buy
it? Chances are I'll spend the next game year or so waiting for crew- even in
systems with millions of people! The Imperial Trader mistype is a crippler in
this respect- I went all the way to Imperial space to get one, because it needed
6 crew. (T.Trader- 5 crew -> I.Trader- 6 crew -> Python- 7 crew, a nice
progression since one crewman is usually quite easy to get) Of course, when I
found this needed only 1 crewman, I was gutted (still bought the ship, because it
looks marvellous, but my chances of ever getting a clipper look lower than ever.)
A simple suggestion is to have a 'crew agency' or allow players to advertise for
crew on the bulletin board. Failing even that, allow 'spare' crew to be
accomodated in Extra Passenger Cabins until required.
 
4) Missiles. Apart from massive great ships and space stations, I have NEVER hit
a ship with a missile, even at point blank range (we are talking Naval Missiles
here!) The enemy ships seem to easily outdistance missiles.

5) Removing equipment. It is VERY ANNOYING to be unable to remove equipment which
a planet does not sell. At the very least, one should be able to have it simply
ripped out (no repayment for this though, obviously.)

That's it for now. Alien races, Generation ships, Space Dredgers, Destructible
Space Stations and suchlike would all be nice, but I feel most of these points
are more important. BTW, the explosion for the big ships like Lynx Bulk Carriers
and Light Cruisers are UTTERLY SILLY, and should be modified. (A screen white-out
followed by TONNES of Metal Alloys and cargo would seem to be a quite nice way
out- of course accompianied by an IMMENSE explosion noise!)

PPS (Sorry but this is such a good prog. that comments flow like water) It would
be INCREDIBLE to be able to fly the aforementioned immense ships. Just a thought.

