I am somewhat disappointed, even though the game looks quite nice.  I
received my copy from Sideline Software ($36) yesterday and it turned
out to be release 1.00.  I have played very little so far, but the
number of bugs popping up is amazing.  For one the docking computer
works only when set at accelerated time (otherwise it kills me).  Also
I have encountered crashes right after running out of fuel and during
combat.

Could a kind person please email me the english non-cracked version
1.02 (which I believe is the most recent version out there)?  I know,
this isn't all too legal, but I don't want to wait for another 6 weeks
to get a replacement copy from GameTEK (they need 4 weeks to deliver,
plus another 2 weeks shipping to the UK).  In a way I feel cheated by
them, how can they send me such a buggy version?

If you want proof that I have my own copy, just ask me questions from
the manual. BTW, my mail server can only handle packages up to 100K,
therefore the uuencoded file should be divided into several ~90K
mailings.

Thanks in advance,

Stefan

