Not a bug.

Try refueling.  Works wonders when you want to go somewhere.  If you coast
into a port on autopilot when your fuel has run out (risky but it can be done)
then your internal fuel tank is empty... even if you buy more fuel and have an
auto refueler it doesn't check so the tank stays empty.  Just go through the
status screens to your cargo list and click the 'refuel' gadget.  Problem
solved.

>(2) Has anyone been able to lock onto Pluto in the Sol system map.
>It never shows any name, just an empty space in the orbital circle.
>If you try to click on it, it never centers. Same problem in other
>systems (mostly objects in far orbit).

Not a bug.

Haven't you noticed that the maps are adjustable?

I'm not talking zooming in and out here... that's basic, but if you hold down
the right mouse button and move the mouse you change the orientation of the
system... so just adjust things so that Pluto is head on right towards you and
then zoom in until you can select it.


Your third item does sound like a genuine bonified insect though.  Not really
TOO much of a problem since it only involves money and there are legitimate
