I've noticed many things said about Frontier that under closer examination
turn out to be untrue;

Myth #1:  Sometimes when you try to launch you don't go anywhere.  This is a
bug and the only way to solve it is to use time acceleration.

Truth:  No, this is rather basic oversight.  The way to solve it is to refuel
your internal tank.  Buying the fuel is not sufficient.  If your tank is empty
you have to go to the f3 cargo screen and click the refuel gadget.

Myth #2:  You never run into more than one enemy at a time.

Truth:  Under max time compression enemies get yanked up close to you to
prevent you zipping past their 'window of oppurtunity' at high speed.  This
causes them to appear one at a time as they get in range.  Moving at a lesser
time compression will cause them to approach normally... and results in packs
of enemy ships.

Myth #3:  It is impossible to dock without the autopilot.

Truth:  Hogwash.  On the four or five occaisions when my autopilot got knocked
out by combat or lack of servicing I still managed to dock just fine manually.
It takes longer and requires fine control, but I've never FAILED to do so...
even when all my maneuvering jets were damaged... space stations, underground
bunkers, and flat landings are all possible.  Only thing I can think of is that
the people who haven't been able to do it are forgetting to put down the
landing gear.

Myth #4:  Once you get up in the game combat is so easy that you can't lose.

Truth:  I had an imperial courier with 20 shield generators taken out by a
single foe in about one second.  I never even saw him as more than a blip on
the scanner.  One of the giant ships like a panther could probably have taken
that... but what about two or three of them?  Besides which... the panther is
hard to destroy because of it's size, but it's just not workable for time
constraints on missions.


Future myth updates as they occur to me.  For the record the bit about no
aliens seems to be true... though I hold out hope for the systems of "Special
Scientific Interest."
-- 
