I was pondering this same question, trying to figure out how difficult
it would be to get to Beta Lyrae, the contact binary star (unexplored,
about 980 or so light years from the Core Systems.) The thing is, if it
takes you more than a year to get there, your drive _is_ going to
fail from lack of servicing! (Don't laugh... this does happen... and
it's embarrassing, not to mention terminal, to see your Class 2 Hyperdrive
replaced with 25 tons of rubbish.)

So traveling out there would require extensive planning, it seems. You'd
need a ship with large cargo capacity, to hold fuel scoop and drive, the
best drive on the market to go over 20 LY in one jump, study the map
to find the most distant frontier system in the direction you're going,
and get the ship serviced there. It should _just_ be possible to make it to
Beta Lyrae; it's in my long-term plans, anyway. And no, I refuse to cheat.

>And another point.
>Last night I got an imperial mission to deliver data cards to a system.
>It was right next door to the imp capital.
>But it had no starports or stations, but it said it had mining operations.
>I took the mission, but on rough (yes I actually managed it!!) landing,
>nothing
>happened.
>How are you supposed to complete the mission?
>I still have the cards, although the time limit has long since expired.
>I tried contacting every planet, no luck!
>Two pirates did attack me on entry though!.

I've noticed that... sometimes you can get a mission to deliver something
to a star system with no settlements. Bizarre. Along the same vein, you
can scroll around the galactic map, find a binary star system with NO
planets, and see it described as "Some mining and ore refinement." Heh.
One wonders where the miners live... of course, perhaps they're in a
little station orbiting a star, mining hydrogen. :) It seems that the
"decide-what-this-system-is-like" routine just checks if there's more
than one body in the system, not if the second body is habitable (or
even a solid planet, as opposed to gas giant or star.)

>Still a great game, no matter what anyone says.....

Amen, brother! The bugs are very annoying, but as far as what the game
is capable of doing, I'm happy with it.

