There is something out there!!!
I was trying to scroll over to another galaxy, after wedging a penny in my shift
and right arrow keys.
After finding out it is simply the same galaxy :( I left it to start scrolling
back to 0,0.
I just glanced at the bottom, and suddenly it said:
Frontier System....

Shit, I scrolled it back, and there it was.
I think it was at -4096,0.
And the name began with a C.
I had a good scroll about and found about 5 others too.
No major starports, but one had an orbital city.
Now all I need it a drive capable of jumping ~200,000 light years. :(

Btw does anyone know which ships can take a fuel scoop.?
My imp courier cant anyway, and I so want to try sun skimming for fuel...

And another point.
Last night I got an imperial mission to deliver data cards to a system.
It was right next door to the imp capital.
But it had no starports or stations, but it said it had mining operations.
I took the mission, but on rough (yes I actually managed it!!) landing, nothing
happened.
How are you supposed to complete the mission?
I still have the cards, although the time limit has long since expired.
I tried contacting every planet, no luck!
Two pirates did attack me on entry though!.

Still a great game, no matter what anyone says.....


Al.


