I've seen lots of complaints recently from people who are getting either
bored with combat in frontier, or narced off about being killed so
quickly. My humble opinion is that offensive weapons are too powerful
relative to defensive (ie shields and hulls). As a case in point I got
shot to bits last night in about 3 seconds flat (Tiger Trader, 20
shields). What got me was that it was all too fast, to begin with I
couldn't see my enemy because the dratted 'ship under attack' message
covered my scanner, and then I couldn't see because my viewscreen was
covered with junk from the enemy lasers. OK you may be saying, so what?
Well, I think that you could put some of the challenge and skill back into
combat (like there was in Elite) by *reducing* the destructive power of all
lasers (yours and enemy) by a factor of 2 or 3. Combats would last longer,
and have more scope for piloting skill, use of missiles etc. The other
advantage of this is that it's (presumably) a fairly easy change to make
to the program. Anyone out there who works out how to do it could post say
the debug commands (for the pc) that make the change, and then everyone
could do it. Anyone game for a spot of hacking?


