Well, after reading this I decided I'd better go home and check.  Sure enough
you can't use the map tilt to get Pluto.  However, you CAN get Pluto... I've
viewed both it and Charon up close.  How you wonder?  Well, it involves moving
the system forward or back in it's rotation until one of the outer planets is
in line with Pluto... then you center on that planet and zoom in.  You can't
get Pluto to appear when you are centered on Sol, but if you center the map on
one of the outer planets (while Pluto is near that planet... rather than on
opposite ends of their orbits) then you can zoom in and tag Pluto.
 
