I don't have any problems with doing it manually.  In fact, often I
turn off the auto pilot, because I can approach a planet faster by
hand than by auto pilot.  This can be very handy when you have some
due date coming up soon. When approaching by hand you can make use of
the stronger forward thrusters for both acceleration and
deacceleration. The actual docking is also much easier in Frontier
compared to Elite, because the on board computer will automatically
rotate your ship when you get close enough.

