Maybe it was a dummy proximity mine -- those don't blow up, although I
suppose it would damage a small ship to run into one. ECM will destroy
ordinary proximity mines.

BTW, here's a solution for those who'd rather run into their pirates in
groups, rather than one-at-a-time: Use the current system map. Select
the dots indicating spacecraft near your current position. Interrogate
them at long range with your communicator icon; if you ask what they're
doing here and they reply "None of your business," they're pirates. Now,
use the autopilot to fly towards _them_! You'll have an indicator on your
screen of how far away they are all the time, so you can crank the time
acceleration slower and slower until you run into them at perhaps only
2 or 3 x normal time... and then they'll come screaming in in a group.
I haven't run into anything bigger than a group of three pirates, but
heck, three is enough for me right now.

Once you've beaten up the pirates, you're free and clear to fly insystem
at maximum time acceleration. I find this is the best workaround for the
pirate bug.

