The best way to get multiple opponents is to do a photo mission and just linger
around over the site.  You need a decent military or naval rank before they'll
give you one of these missions, but they are great fun... you CAN sneak in and
get the pictures and blast out before they have any time to react... but it's
alot more enjoyable to just hover over the base for a half hour or so until
you've got something like 100+ enemies weaving all around you.

NOT recommended for those with small ships.  I've traded in my Imperial Courier
for a Tiger Trader with class 5 hyperdrive (more range on jumps was the
important factor).  I've got 17 shields, a 4 MW beam front mounted, and a
turreted 30 MW mining laser.  The above sort of enemy cloud (which includes all
sorts of ships... not just vipers like in police attacks) is survivable with
little or no damage... provided I don't mess up.  Keep going in a straight line
for more than 5 seconds and you've had it.
