I tried out that method, but it fails too often for me.  Once you
activate the auto pilot, it seems that not only can you aim very
easily at the enemy, but so can the enemy him/her-self.  50% of the
time I get blown up myself before I managed to land a good shot.  My
best tactic is to do it all by hand...  just aim and shoot with full
thrusters.  With that method I almost never get any damage (especially
if I have a small and fast ship).  It is difficult to land a hit on
the small ships, but since they don't have any shields, every hit
counts on their hull. The bigger the ships, the easier it is to
hit them. Only problem with the bigger ships becomes the shield.
 
