arriving at the port, don't know if it would count as a kill to get them
BEFORE the appointed time.

2:  Wait until the appropriate time.  This can be a problem... in ONE of my
assassinations they were charging me with 'piracy and murder' two days before
the event.  If this is the case you've probably lost your shot.

3:  About a minute (or as many as 20) before the time listed on the roster
leave the port.  Fly out (and a little to the side so they don't run into you)
and kill your engines.  Then turn around.

4:  At the exact second listed on the roster the enemy ship will appear.
Target your tracking tunnel on him and get ready to follow through hyperspace
(you need a hyperspace cloud analyzer).  Sometimes he will stay in the same
system... in this case follow until you are out of range of the space station
and then kill him.  If you do not see him leaving at the appropriate time you
may be too far from the station... target the station itself and check the
radar mapper and hyperspace cloud analyzer... if either shows a reading you
have him and can follow as per the above.

5:  Once you've gone through hyperspace find the target.  The analyzer lists
both destination and arrival TIME.  This is important.  If you get there before
him find his arrival cloud and get to it... then, when he appears pounce on him
immediatly.  Otherwise, check the map and find his location... should be on a
line between you and the port he is heading for.  Use autopilot to close in on
him and destroy.

Do not:  Attack while near a starport, leave the base AFTER the appointed time,
or wait outside for a prolonged period.  Saved games are also useful when doing
this sort of mission... there are often unforseen problems that can only be
fixed by backing up (like the target jumping to a system outside your range).
