Well, I had a hunt around last night in Frontier. I wanted to find
Beta Lyrae, the touching binary star system which is shown on the
galaxy map, but is a very long way from Sol. This system should by
rights be one of the most interesting in the game.

After searching for about 15 mins I found it -- it is in sector
[-146,85].

"Great!", I thought. "I can view it." However, it is an unexplored
system. Luckily, there was a wormhole to a star about 20 Lys
from it. :-) I stripped down my Panther, loaded it up with fuel and
took off.

Half a dozen jumps later I was just about to hyperspace to Beta Lyrae
itself. I decided to save the game at this point, which was a good
thing, because when I made the final jump, my Amiga crashed!

"Ok", I thought, "this was probably bad timing." So I tried it again.
And again. And again. It always crashes.

AAAAAaaaaaarrrrrrrrrrrgggggggggggggghhhhhhhhhhhhh!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

Let me rant at this point:

WHENEVER YOU TRY TO HYPERSPACE TO THE MOST INTERESTING STAR SYSTEM
IN THE ENTIRE FRONTIER GALAXY, THE BLOODY GAME CRASHES! 

I am, to put it mildly, annoyed. If anybody wants to replicate this
bug, I have Amiga Frontier version 1.0, my machine is an A2000 with
hard drive (GVP) and a 16MhZ 68020 accelerator with FPU.

If you like, I could post my save file in a uuencoded form to this
group, and everybody could try it. Maybe somebody can get it to
work, and they could tell all of us about it.

Alternatively, maybe I have found the Frontier aliens -- and they
have a weapon which kills anyone who enters their system. :-)

Regards,


Tom Nettleship (Average/Master/Sergeant/Mighty Pissed Off)



P.S. Just how COULD David Braben have let this one slip through?
     I am stunned by the amount of insectoid life in Frontier. If
     it wasn't for the game's massive scope, I would be very
     disappointed with my purchase.

