Well, a friend of mine just bought the Amiga version, and we looked
through for the version string: V1.05! This is the highest version I
have heard of yet.

I took a copy (to upgrade my *purchased* V1.00 -- perfectly legal in
my book). As far as I can tell, there is little difference. I have
noticed the following things:

    Beta Lyrae bug : Still in there. Not surprising as I was the first
                     one to report it here, and maybe David hasn't got
                     the news / fixed it yet. :-(
    Wormhole bug   : Still in there.
    Bulletin bug   : Still in there. This surprised me. It should be a
                     trivial fix -- make sure the 'top' pointer / counter
                     is reset on docking.
    Colour flashing: Seems to have been improved / tweaked slightly. The
                     space clouds no longer flash to dark as much, but they
                     occasionally flash to a lighter colour now. :-)
    Relative-to bug: You know -- the autopilot staying rel. to a star,
                     resulting in overshoot of the planet / space-station.
                     This one seems to have been improved. It happens
                     less often, though it still does.

Also, there is no sign of space aliens / thargoids / Fer-de-lance cruisers /
black holes / other galaxies / cloud cities / more interesting missions, but
then that's not very likely anyway.

IMHO, David Braben is probably sunning himself on a beach in Hawaii right
now (if he isn't, he deserves to be) and letting somebody else fix all the
little bugs.

Regards,

Tom Nettleship
(Above average / Sir / Private / *Slightly* less pissed off)


