I thought I might try to sum up all bugs found in Frontier. Feel free to add
new bugs should you find one. If you do, remember to write which version of
the game you have.


BUGS I'VE ENCOUNTERED IN FRONTIER V1.00


BUG: Messed up bulletin board.

DESCRIPTION: Sometimes the bulletin board will contain the Stockmarket list
      or Shipyards list instead of the usual messages. Apparently this
      is due to an overflow when the last list you looked at was longer
      than the bulletin board message list.

FIX: Always scroll to topmost message/item in any list before going to
     other spaceport OR fast forward to next day.

---

BUG: The Wormhole Bug.

DESCRIPTION: Using the map and SHIFT/ARROWing away from your current system,
             you will occasionally get 'FUEL NEEDED XX TONS' instead of the
             correct 'OUT OF RANGE', and due to this, you can hyperspace
             across the entire galaxy with a single jump. It seems the
             places you can jump to are placed at certain fixed intervals
             from your starting position.

FIX: Don't use it.

---

BUG: Autopilot stops on a dime.

DESCRIPTION: When you're heading towards a target, you can accelerate
             manually to very high speeds, and when you're very close to
             the target enable the autopilot. Defying the laws of nature,
             the autopilot will bring you to an immediate halt.

FIX: Don't use it.

---

BUG: Autopilot crashes.

DESCRIPTION: If you let the autopilot dock your ship at normal speed, it
             will frequently crash the ship by hitting the surface/station.
             The same is true if you let the autopilot fly you from one
             spaceport to another on the same planet.

FIX: Use accelerated time when docking or moving between spaceports.

---

BUG: The Beta Lyrae bug.

DESCRIPTION: Hyperspacing into the Beta Lyrae system (-146,85) hangs the
             computer. I've tested different kickstarts and ships, but the
             result is always the same - which is a shame since it is one
             of the most interesting systems in the game. A saved game with
             a ship within jumping distance of Beta Lyrae is available.

FIX: None known.

---

BUG: Sometimes impossible to take off from pressurized spaceports.

DESCRIPTION: Sometimes when you're trying to take off from a spaceport on
             a planet without air, you will not be able to gain height.
             This MIGHT not be a bug, since there might be a number of
             reasons why you can't take off, but I do know that sometimes
             you cannot take off normally even with lots of fuel in the
             tank.

FIX: Various, ranging from the brutal (get 99 shields and drive
     through the wall) to the hopeful (use accelerated time OR pull up
     the nose hard while giving thrust).

---

BUG: Missiles can be fired from within stations.

DESCRIPTION: One can lock onto targets using the map, and then fire ones
             missiles although one is docked. Since all other weapons are
             disabled when docked, this is probably a bug.

FIX: Don't.

---

BUG: One enemy at the time.

DESCRIPTION: You will NEVER get more than one enemy at a time if you're
             travelling with the highest time acceleration.

FIX: I don't know. I've only once met more than one enemy at the same time,
     and I honestly don't know how I did it. Possibly if you use no/low
     accelerated time? Possibly not a bug.

---

BUG: The Exit bug.

DESCRIPTION: Pressing EXIT doesn't return you to Workbench, it just returns
             you to the intro animation.

FIX: A patch has been posted to usenet by Teemu Suikki (not connected to
     the original programmers of Frontier AFAIK). It enables exiting
     to workbench by pressing X.

---

BUG: The Multi Galaxy bug.

DESCRIPTION: If you zoom out long enough in the Galactic map, you will see
             many galaxies in a neat grid. Patiently moving the target
             cursor into one of these galaxies reveals that they're really
             our own galaxy.

FIX: None known.

---

BUG: Systems with Import&Export - but no planets and no ports.

DESCRIPTION: Sometimes info on a system will show that it has import and
             export even though there's no planets or ports in the system.
             I've only seen it in binary, tertiary and so on systems.

---

That about wraps it up for bugs I've encountered personally. More bugs have
been reported though.

BUGS I'VE NOT SEEN PERSONALLY:


BUG: Turrets firing at self.

DESCRIPTION: Turret mounted lasers/plasmas can fire on ones own ship.

FIX: Don't use turrets.

---

BUG: Negative value on precious metals.

DESCRIPTION: In one system, I believe it's Cemiess, precious metals cost
             -1500cr. This means you are PAID to take them off their hands.
             Mind you, this might not be a bug.

FIX: Don't trade in precious metals on Cemiess.

---

BUG: Getting paid when selling ship - and keeping the ship.

DESCRIPTION: If you've got a passenger in your ship, you cannot sell the
             ship. However, you will still get _money_ if you trade in an
             expensive ship for a cheap one, meaning that you can sell your
             ship as many times as you wish and still have it.

FIX: Don't. Probably the most boring way there is to get rich.

---

BUG: Missions to systems without a spaceport or station.

DESCRIPTION: When running errands for the Military/Navy, one will sometimes
             be asked to carry objects to systems which does not have a
             spaceport or spacestation, making it impossible to complete
             the mission.

FIX: None known.

---


