I thought I'd try to compile a list of all the features I feel are missing
or badly implemented in Frontier. Feel free to add your own.


--------------- THE OPPOSITION --------------------

*SMARTER ENEMIES!

The enemies have the intellect of termites! It's pure dumb luck should they
ever hit you, and if they have a chance, they'll crash into eachother, you, or
unfortunate nearby planets. I can understand that behaviour from large, well
shielded ships - but from _Fighters_???


*BADDER ENEMIES!

Even though there ARE a few pretty tough cookies out there, the vast majority
are small one-man fighters with pulse lasers. After a while, it just gets
boring running over them (I can't even be bothered to target them anymore; I
just let them crash me).


*MORE ENEMIES!

One only encounters the enemies one by one. None of them's good enough to
put up a fight against a well equipped large ship by their own.


*THARGOIDS!

WHERE ARE THE THARGOIDS?!? This ancient, evil, insectoid race were the only
ones who could give you a run for the money in Elite - surely the Federal
Navy hasn't defeated them? Imagine fleets of Thargoid battleships and cruisers 
attacking
the human space, imagine leading a division of warships against them..!


*FLEETS!

If there's to be no Thargoids, atleast the Empire and the Federation should
battle it out somewhere. Frontier needs some real large-scale mayhem!


*TOUGHER POLICE!

The police in Frontier is pitiful - they're far more likely to hurt eachother
than any wrong-doers. Install shields on all Viper policeships, and remove the
blindfold the pilots (seems) to have. Yesterday I watched 20+ policeships fail
to lauch out of a spacestation - not a single one made it into open space. I
didn't fire a shot, and I didn't get a scratch.



-------------- GENERAL STUFF ---------------------

*MISSIONS!

Frontier needs Elite-style missions to keep the player interested.


*BETTER MINES AND MISSILES!

They are utterly useless as it is. Couldn't hit the broadside of a
planet.


*FIND: FUNCTION!

It can be a real pain to find the system you want to go to. How about a FIND
command like the one in Elite?


*LESS POWERFUL WEAPONS AND DEFENCES _OR_ BETTER EQUIPPED ENEMIES!

Buy a largish ship. Put a lot of shields and a big gun in - and presto,
you are now invulnerable. You can equip yourself to the point where
you can *drive* through all opposition, including space stations.


*ALIENS!

Why not scatter a few alien empires throughout the galaxy? It's big enough.


*EXPLORATION!

There's untold numbers of 'unexplored, no data available' systems in the
Milky Way. Why not let the player explore systems, optionally even naming
the planets? And, offcourse, there should always be the possibility to find
something, like an alien race with strange new technology. Even if there
would only be something interesting on one out of every thousand planets, it
would still give the game great staying power.


*LONG RANGE BATTLE!

It should be possible to zoom the normal view, and atleast some lasers should
be able to hit targets much further away than 8km.


*THE LONG RANGE CRUISERS AND LYNXES SHOULD BE TOUGHER AND EXPLODE BETTER!
Taking out a long range cruiser is easy, and produces a pitiful explosion
and no cargo. Why not white-out the screen when it explodes, and have
hundreds of tonnes of cargo scatter about. Offcourse, they should have many
shields, heavy artillery and a few defending fighters aswell.


*BETTER SOUND!

The quality of the samples in the music is poor.


*FIX THE BUGS!!!




I still love the game, though. Too bad it wasn't ready when it was released.


